160
00:12:29,414 --> 00:12:34,123
{\an1}Come on, don't go! You
guys, stick around and
play with me!

161
00:12:34,724 --> 00:12:41,369
{\an1}Well, it took an idiot like that
to stop all that ruckus& Hm.
Sort of  reminds me of someone.

162
00:12:41,403 --> 00:12:44,008
Yeah... Naruto.
Don't you think
so too, Lee?

163
00:12:44,042 --> 00:12:46,012
Huh? Hey, Lee?

164
00:12:46,046 --> 00:12:48,482
{\an1}<i>(Lee)</i>
<i>Excuse me,</i>
<i>please wait!</i>

165
00:12:48,516 --> 00:12:54,828
{\an1}I realized when we made
contact, that you are quite
different than all the others.

166
00:12:56,664 --> 00:12:59,369
{\an7}You were able to stop my
attack so easily back there.

167
00:12:59,402 --> 00:13:03,343
{\an7}It may sound arrogant
to say this, but

168
00:13:03,376 --> 00:13:05,881
{\an7}it takes someone
extraordinary to do
something like that!

169
00:13:05,915 --> 00:13:11,524
{\an7}That is how I can tell. that
you have had to overcome
great odds like me.

170
00:13:11,558 --> 00:13:13,395
{\an1}What are you saying?

171
00:13:13,428 --> 00:13:16,467
Well, that you
and I are alike.

172
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,504
I know about you, too.

173
00:13:18,537 --> 00:13:22,144
You're Rock Lee
of the Hidden Leaf.

174
00:13:22,177 --> 00:13:25,249
I'm Shira of the
Hidden Sand.

175
00:13:25,282 --> 00:13:27,855
Shira... Huh?

176
00:13:27,888 --> 00:13:31,695
I don't know what you
sensed back there, but...

177
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:34,333
{\an1}...dwelling on the misfortunes
of birth is meaningless.

178
00:13:34,366 --> 00:13:38,775
